  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (cd8da50 2022-12-30T11:15:16.421114784Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nI have recently migrated my test suite to forge, and there is one test which is failing due to a storage key that is not persisting correctly:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n\r\n/* Already inside delegatecall */\r\n\r\n_storage[key] = val;\r\n\r\nconsole.log(\"a\", _storage[key], address(this));\r\n// a 453347196099381287746848 0x34A1D3fff3958843C43aD80F30b94c510645C316\r\n\r\nconsole.log(\"b\", _storage[key], address(this));\r\n// b 453347196099381287746848 0x34A1D3fff3958843C43aD80F30b94c510645C316\r\n\r\n/* delegatecall returns */\r\n\r\nconsole.log(\"c\", _storage[key], address(this));\r\n// c 0 0x34A1D3fff3958843C43aD80F30b94c510645C316                       \r\n\r\nconsole.log(\"d\", _storage[key], address(this));\r\n// d 0 0x34A1D3fff3958843C43aD80F30b94c510645C316                       \r\n```\r\n\r\nI'm confident that this is a bug in the VM because it works in the other test environment, and the exact code path where the discrepancy is produced has not changed:\r\n\r\n```\r\naddEdgeStorage(from.id, slot, edge);                            \r\nconsole.log(\"b\", _edges[10000000000001], address(this));        \r\n                                                                   \r\nreturn (AddEdgeResult.Added, encodeEdge(edge));                 \r\n \r\n...\r\n\r\n(bool ok, bytes memory rdata) = backend.delegatecall(call);\r\nif (ok) {                                                 \r\n  console.log(\"c\", _edges[10000000000001], address(this));\r\n}                                                         \r\n```\r\n\r\n",
